<p>
<seg id=1> On the AIDS Day, the US president Clinton promised to provide new assistance to preventing this deadly disease, including more research funds. </seg>
<seg id=2> Clinton planned to increase AIDS research by increasing funds by 30% for the National Hygiene Center. </seg>
<seg id=3> He also announced that he plans to provide 10,000,000 US dollars to support orphans of those who died from Aids </seg>
<seg id=4> The Clinton Government expressed that the increased research fund is the largest investment of public funds ever given at one time towards Aids research. </seg>
</p>
